lit link as the link could fail resulting in an unsafe riding condition leading to loss of control and an accident."}]},{"node":"text","body":" "}],"severity":"warning","type":"general"}]}]},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"},{"node":"image","body":[],"type":"svg"}],"ancestors":["1343233163"],"parent":"1343233163","lastUpdate":"2023-11-13T10:42:02.000Z","metadata":{"markets":["All"],"_id":"65c772818dab24d43a9e9868"},"search":["Drive Chain Replacement","Make sure the motorcycle is stabilised and adequately supported.","Do not support the motorcycle on any ancillary component, the exhaust system or any other non structural parts of the motorcycle frame.","A correctly supported motorcycle will help prevent it from falling.","An unstable motorcycle may fall resulting in motorcycle damage, serious injury or death.","The following instructions for the replacement of rivet link type drive chains requires the use of ","37104435 - CI - Drive Chain Riveting Tool",".","Service tool body","Allen keys","Small pressure screw","Spring","Cutting pin","Riveting pin","Hollow cutting block","Link plate block","Riveting V block","Guide block","Support the motorcycle on a stand so the rear wheel is clear of the ground.","Insert the hollow cutting block into the chain tool body so that the channel is facing towards the large pressure screw as shown and secure with the securing feature.","Proprietary chain tool body","Large pressure screw","Hollow cutting block","Securing feature","Lock nuts","Position the chain tool to the chain making sure that the link pin which is to be removed is aligned with the holes in the hollow cutting block and the large pressure screw. ","Tighten the large pressure screw by hand to grip the chain.","Secure the locking nuts.","Proprietary chain tool body","Large pressure screw","Chain","Hollow cutting block","Locking nuts","Insert the cutting pin into the spring.","Insert the spring and cutting pin assembly into the large pressure screw.","Insert the small pressure screw into the large pressure screw until the cutting pin contacts the link pin that is being removed.","Retain the tool body then tighten the small pressure screw until the link pin is pressed out from the chain. Do not exceed ","15 Nm",".","Make sure that the cutting pin is centralised on the link pin to be removed.","Proprietary chain tool body","Small pressure screw","Chain","Repeat steps 3 to 9 on the remaining link pin.","Remove the tool and separate the two ends of the chain, collecting the link plate.","Remove the hollow cutting block from the chain tool body.","Remove the small pressure screw, spring and cutting pin from the large pressure screw. ","The replacement chain is supplied in a split condition, complete with a link kit to join the two ends.","The component parts of the new link kit are coated with a special grease which must not be removed.","Removal of this special grease will severely reduce the service life of the chain.","Use the old drive chain to pull the new chain into position as follows: Temporarily attach the end of the new chain to a free end of the old chain using the old connector link. Carefully pull the other end of the old chain to pull the new chain around the sprockets.","Do not use the new connector link as the special grease on it may be removed.","Using the new link supplied with the chain kit, join the two ends of the chain. Make sure that the O-rings are positioned as shown below and the link plate is fitted with its markings facing outwards.","O-rings","Link","Link plate","Insert the guide block into the chain tool body so that the channel is facing towards the large pressure screw as shown and secure with the securing feature.","Proprietary chain tool body","Large pressure screw","Guide block","Securing feature","Lock nuts","Position the tool to the chain.","Position the raised heads on the outer face of the new link into the channel of the guide block.","Position the link plate block centrally to the link plate.","Tighten the large pressure screw by hand so that the guide block and link plate block grip the chain.","Secure the lock nuts.","Proprietary chain tool body","Link plate block","Link plate","Link","Large pressure screw","Lock nuts","Insert the riveting pin into the spring.","Insert the spring and riveting pin assembly into the large pressure screw","Insert the small pressure screw into the large pressure screw until the riveting pin contacts the link plate block.","Retain the tool body and tighten the small pressure screw to ","15 Nm",".","Proprietary chain tool body","Small pressure screw","Chain","Back off the small pressure screw and release the lock nuts.","Release the large pressure screw, collect the link plate block and remove the tool assembly.","Make sure the link plate is correctly assembled and pressed fully onto the link.","Link plate ","Link pins","Reposition the tool so that the raised heads on the outer face of the new link fit into the channel of the guide block","Position the riveting V block centrally, in a horizontal orientation, to one of the pin heads on the outer face on the new link.","Tighten the large pressure screw by hand so that the riveting V block and guide block grip the chain.","Retain the tool body and tighten the small pressure screw to ","20 Nm ",".","Proprietary chain tool body","Small pressure screw","Large pressure screw","Riveting V block","Guide block","Link plate","Lock nuts","Chain","Repeat steps 29 to 32 for the remaining pin head.","Check the new link heads are both riveted horizontally.","Link plate","Pin heads - Horizontally riveted","Reposition the tool so that the raised heads on the outer face of the new link fit into the channel of the guide block","Position the riveting V block centrally, in a vertical orientation, to one of the pin heads on the outer face on the new link.","Tighten the large pressure screw by hand so that the riveting V block and guide block grip the chain.","Retain the tool body and tighten the small pressure screw to ","20 Nm ",".","Proprietary chain tool body","Small pressure screw","Large pressure screw","Riveting V block","Guide block","Link plate","Lock nuts","Chain","Repeat steps 35 to 38 for the remaining pin head.","Remove the tool and check that the link pins are correctly riveted.","Link plate","Riveted pin heads","If either split link pin is not correctly riveted, the split link must be removed and replaced with a new link. Never operate the motorcycle with an incorrectly riveted split link as the link could fail resulting in an unsafe riding condition leading to loss of control and an accident."],"viewCount":2,"infoType":"InfoType04","views":[{"createdBy":"65cbd6374e7861d9b7ef1813","createdAt":"2024-01-18T14:47:25.427Z","_id":"65e79b6a8dab24d43af4d1b0"},{"createdBy":"65b383f4c20ee762077d6e4e","createdAt":"2024-02-14T19:29:53.177Z","_id":"65e94842e919dffe56c04783"}],"createdAt":"2024-02-10T12:56:33.793Z","updatedAt":"2024-03-07T04:53:22.419Z","__v":0,"updatedBy":"65b383f4c20ee762077d6e4e"}